Subject: [PATCH] ppu/include: remove sys/select.h shim

PSL1GHT shipped ppu/include/sys/select.h as a one-liner that pulled in
<net/select.h>.  That worked with newlib 1.20, whose sys/types.h did not
transitively include <sys/select.h>, but newlib ≥2.x pulls sys/select.h
from inside sys/types.h under __BSD_VISIBLE (default on).  The shim then
drags in <net/select.h> → <signal.h> → <sys/signal.h>, which in turn
references pid_t before sys/types.h has finished declaring it — the
preprocessor is reentering a half-built header.  Every translation unit
that indirectly pulls sys/types.h breaks at crt1.c.

The shim has no callers inside PSL1GHT (ppu/librt/socket.c and
ppu/sprx/libnet/socket.c include <net/select.h> directly), so deleting
it is safe.  External consumers that want network select should include
<net/select.h> explicitly — this also matches the intent of the split.

diff --git a/ppu/include/sys/select.h b/ppu/include/sys/select.h
deleted file mode 100644
--- a/ppu/include/sys/select.h
+++ /dev/null
@@ -1 +0,0 @@
-#include <net/select.h>
